 {"id":"br-2tnl.5.10.3","title":"T5.10.3: Implement full progressive refinement workflow","description":"## Problem Statement

The current `TwoTierBridge::search()` (search_service.rs:633-681) only implements fast-only search:

```rust
// For now, use simple similarity search on the fast tier
// Full progressive refinement will be added in a follow-up
let hits = self.index().search_fast(&embedding, limit);
```

The progressive refinement workflow exists in `two_tier.rs` (`TwoTierSearchIter`) but is not wired into the bridge.

## Background: Two-Tier Progressive Search

The intended architecture from the bake-off:

```
User Query
    │
    ├──→ [Fast Embedder] ──→ Results in ~1ms (display immediately)
    │       (potion-128M)
    │
    └──→ [Quality Model] ──→ Refined scores in ~130ms
             (MiniLM-L6)           │
                                   ▼
                           Smooth re-rank
```

**Key insight**: Don't block on quality embedding. Return fast results immediately, then refine in background.

## Implementation Strategy

### Phase Model

The `SearchPhase` enum already exists in two_tier.rs:

```rust
pub enum SearchPhase {
    Initial { results: Vec<ScoredResult>, latency_ms: u64 },
    Refined { results: Vec<ScoredResult>, latency_ms: u64 },
    RefinementFailed { error: String },
}
```

### Integration Options

**Option A: Synchronous Two-Phase (simpler)**
1. Return fast results immediately via sync API
2. Block on quality refinement (acceptable for CLI/MCP)
3. Return refined results or fall back to initial

**Option B: Async/Streaming (advanced)**
1. Return initial results via channel/stream
2. Spawn background task for quality refinement
3. Push refined results when ready
4. Client decides whether to wait

**Recommended**: Start with Option A (synchronous), design for Option B upgrade.

## Implementation Plan

### Step 1: Expose searcher from bridge
```rust
impl TwoTierBridge {
    pub fn create_searcher(&self) -> Option<TwoTierSearcher<'_>> {
        get_two_tier_context().create_searcher(&*self.index())
    }
}
```

### Step 2: Wire progressive search into bridge
```rust
pub fn search_progressive(&self, query: &SearchQuery, limit: usize) 
    -> impl Iterator<Item = SearchPhase> 
{
    let searcher = self.create_searcher()?;
    searcher.search(&query.text, limit)
}
```

### Step 3: Update orchestration to consume phases
```rust
fn try_two_tier_search(query: &SearchQuery, limit: usize) -> Option<Vec<SearchResult>> {
    let bridge = get_two_tier_bridge()?;
    let mut final_results = None;

    for phase in bridge.search_progressive(query, limit) {
        match phase {
            SearchPhase::Initial { results, .. } => {
                final_results = Some(convert_results(results));
            }
            SearchPhase::Refined { results, .. } => {
                final_results = Some(convert_results(results));
            }
            SearchPhase::RefinementFailed { error } => {
                tracing::warn!(error = %error, "quality refinement failed");
            }
        }
    }
    final_results
}
```

### Step 4: Add configuration controls
```rust
pub struct TwoTierSearchConfig {
    /// Whether to skip quality refinement
    pub fast_only: bool,
    /// Maximum time to wait for quality refinement
    pub quality_timeout_ms: u64,
    /// Weight for quality scores in blending
    pub quality_weight: f32,
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `TwoTierBridge::search()` returns progressive results
- [ ] Initial results returned in <5ms (fast embedding latency)
- [ ] Quality refinement improves relevance when available
- [ ] Graceful degradation when quality embedder unavailable
- [ ] Configuration controls for fast-only mode
- [ ] Metrics: initial_latency_ms, refinement_latency_ms, was_refined

## Test Plan

1. Unit test: Progressive search yields Initial then Refined phases
2. Unit test: Fast-only config skips refinement
3. Unit test: Quality unavailable yields RefinementFailed
4. Integration test: End-to-end search with refinement
5. Benchmark: Verify fast results in <5ms

## Files to Modify

- `crates/mcp-agent-mail-search-core/src/two_tier.rs`
  - Already has `TwoTierSearcher`, `SearchPhase`
  - May need config refinements

- `crates/mcp-agent-mail-search-core/src/auto_init.rs`
  - `TwoTierContext::create_searcher()` already exists

- `crates/mcp-agent-mail-db/src/search_service.rs`
  - `TwoTierBridge::search()` - wire progressive
  - `try_two_tier_search()` - consume phases

## Dependencies

